{#- ### Top Mitigations — single ranked table with a dedicated Component column.

    Layout (2026-05-29 — user request: the per-component group label used to
    sit in an in-table divider row `| **↳ Component …** | | | | |`, which most
    renderers show as one cell jammed into the `#`/ID column with four empty
    trailing cells — it looked displaced. It now lives in its own `Component`
    column, repeated on every row (2026-05-29 follow-up: once-per-group blanks
    read as a missing value when a bucket spans many rows) so the table reads
    as grouped-by-component while every row carries its own component value.
    This also matches the sibling Top Findings table, which already
    carries a Component column.

    2026-06-03 — the dedicated `Priority` column was dropped: the rollout
    priority now rides on the linked mitigation itself, emitted by
    `linkify_with_label(m.id)` so every fully-linked measure across the report
    carries it consistently. A standalone column would duplicate it.
    2026-06-04 — Variant B: a single monochrome circled digit whose number is
    the priority (`❶` … `❹`), the colourless parallel to the findings circle.):

      | # | Component             | Mitigation             | Addresses | Effort |
      |---|---|---|---|---|
      | 1 | **Express Backend (…)**   | ❶ [M-001](#m-001) — … | ...       | ...    |
      | 2 | **Express Backend (…)**   | ❶ [M-002](#m-002) — … | ...       | ...    |
      | 3 | **Angular SPA (…)**       | ❷ [M-003](#m-003) — … | ...       | ...    |

    Inputs:
      groups    : list of { header, component_label, divider_label,
                            include_affects_column, mitigations[] }
                  - component_label: plain bucket label ("Express Backend (c-id)"
                                     or "Cross-cutting") for the Component column
                  - mitigations[]: data rows with continuous global numbering
                                   { number, id, title, primary_component_id,
                                     addresses[{ref,label}], effort, priority }
                                   Pre-sorted: P1 → P2, severity, effort, ID.
                                   (priority still drives the sort; it is just
                                   no longer rendered as its own column.)
      intro     : top-of-section paragraph string (mentions §9 register)
      footer    : optional italic footer line under the table (may be None)
-#}
